---
import GateMotion from '../assets/gate-motion.svg';

// `base` (the universal floor) is intentionally not surfaced here — it's
// merged under every rulebook implicitly, not a rulebook a user selects.
const RULEBOOKS = [
  {
    name: 'swe',
    line: 'Software engineering: no claim without a fresh test behind it, no commit on a protected branch, no secret in the diff.',
  },
  {
    name: 'skill-authoring',
    line: 'For repos that write agent skills: nothing ships as verified without a fresh evaluation of the exact text being shipped.',
  },
];

const AUTHORING = 'https://github.com/sorawit-w/kerby/blob/main/docs/AUTHORING-RULEBOOKS.md';
---

<section id="what" aria-labelledby="what-heading">
  <h2 id="what-heading">One motion. Any work.</h2>

  <GateMotion class="gate-motion" />

  <ol class="steps mono">
    <li>GATE — an action arrives and stops at the threshold.</li>
    <li>WEIGH — kerby checks it against the evidence: tests, diffs, approvals.</li>
    <li>VERDICT — it passes, or it doesn't. There is no third option.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    The engine is domain-blind. It loads a rulebook, watches the work, and renders verdicts. It
    doesn't know what coding is.
  </p>
  <p>
    A rulebook is a folder: the rules for one kind of work, plus the checks that enforce them. Load
    the one that fits. Write your own when it doesn't. Rulebooks from outside your machine pass a
    one-time trust review before they can run.
  </p>

  <ul class="cards">
    {RULEBOOKS.map((r) => (
      <li class="card">
        <span class="card-name mono">{r.name}</span>
        <span class="card-line">{r.line}</span>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>

  <p class="closing">
    The engine is finished machinery. The next rulebook is a folder you write.
    {' '}<a href={AUTHORING}>Write a rulebook →</a>
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .gate-motion {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--structure);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .cards {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .cards {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-content: start;
  }

  .card-name {
    color: var(--structure);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .card-line {
    color: var(--secondary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .mono {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
</style>
